Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thatâs delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. editorialNotes.standard: Once again, the creators of The Human Body and Simple Machines have turned playtime into a rich learning experience.
